= Altnet Seeks Patent Royalties from Filesharing Networks =
->
[ [:SwpikxraniEn: Patents in Action]
| [:SwpatcninoEn: Patent News]
| [http://gauss.ffii.org/PatWIKI/EP826181/Comments EP826181]
]
----

Altnet Inc, an company affiliated with Kazaa, is seeking patent royalties from competitors of Kazaa who use a commmon technique called filename hashing. 

== News, Chronology, Media Echo ==

 * 2005-01-13 US [http://www.theinquirer.net/?article=20681 The Inquirer: We own file sharing code claim]
 * 2005-01-13 US [http://news.google.com/news?hl=en&ie=UTF-8&scoring=d&q=%22Patents+Pressed+Against+File-Sharing+Networks%22+%22washington+post%22&btnG=Search+News Washington Post: Patents Pressed Against File-Sharing Networks]
 * 2005-01-12 US [http://news.com.com/Altnet+seeks+patent+royalties+from+P2P/2100-1030_3-5534087.html CNet: Altnet seeks patent royalties from P2P]
 * 2005-01-12 WW [http://zgp.org/pipermail/p2p-hackers/2005-January/002304.html Ian Clarke: Altnet goes after p2p networks with obvious patent]
 * 2005-01-12 US [http://p2pnet.net/story/3512 P2Pnet: Altnet tries TrueNames on p2p ops]
 * 2005-01-12 US [http://p2pnet.net/story/3527 P2Pnet: Altnet 'extortion' attempt]
 * 2005-01-12 WW [http://p2pnet.net/story/3533 P2Pnet: Altnet has vowed to protect its claims by all available means, including litigation]
 * 2005-01-12 US [http://www.bizreport.com/news/8573/ Washington Post: Letter Applies Peer-to-Peer Pressure] (partners of the Kazaa network claim they have patents that cover most of peer-to-peer networking)

